<item>
            <title>[LU-18820] Interop sanity-sec test_27a: Long fileset causes line break with &quot;lctl get_param&quot;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18820</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/56757/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/56757/&lt;/a&gt; introduced a IAM support for nodemap filesets. In this context, the fileset length in sanity-sec 27a was signficantly increased to test multiple fileset fragments on the IAM. This long fileset is also used in interop with &quot;lctl set_param -P&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, running &quot;lctl get_param&quot; with this long fileset on older servers (&amp;lt;= 2.15) causes a line break which causes &quot;wait_nm_sync&quot; to fail when comparing the expected vs. the actual output:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;MGS
nodemap.default.fileset=/thisisaverylongsubdirtotestlongfilesetsandtotestmultiplefilesetfragmentsonthenodemapiam_default
OTHER - IP: 10.240.44.82
nodemap.default.fileset= /thisisaverylongsubdirtotestlongfilesetsandtotestmultiplefilesetfragmentsonthenodemapiam_default
 sanity-sec test_27a: @@@@@@ FAIL: mgs and default fileset mismatch, 10 attempts 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="88339">LU-18820</key>
